HEADWORD: Kattimundoo
<hw>Kat`ti*mun"doo</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
caoutchouc-like substance obtained from the milky juice of the East
Indian <spn>Euphorbia Kattimundoo</spn>. It is used as a
cement.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

